<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-02-13.S3W-20536.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80317" speakername="Marlyn Glen (North East Scotland) (Lab)" spid="S3W-20536" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa0213.htm#6">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what the MMR vaccination uptake rate was in NHS Tayside in each of the last three years, broken down by community health partnership.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-02-13.S3W-20536.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80379" speakername="Shona Robison" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa0213.htm#6">

  <p>MMR vaccination uptake rates by community health partnership are published on the Information Service Division (ISD) Scotland website under Child Health at:</p>

  <p><a href="http://www.isdscotland.org/isd/ch-immunisation.jsp?pContentID=5407&amp;p_applic=CCC&amp;p_service=Content.show&amp;" target="_blank">http://www.isdscotland.org/isd/ch-immunisation.jsp?pContentID=5407&amp;p_applic=CCC&amp;p_service=Content.show&amp;</a>.</p>

  <p>Data is available by calendar year for 2006 and 2007 and by quarter from the period ending 30 June 2006 to 30 September 2008. Data for the quarter and calendar year ending 31 December 2008 will be published at the end of March 2009.</p>

</reply>
